relationship underscores the fact

00:09:19.330 --> 00:09:21.050
that each time we use antibiotics,

00:09:21.050 --> 00:09:26.020
we potentially fuel the
growth of superbugs.

00:09:26.020 --> 00:09:30.030
And Stuart Levy, one of my heroes

00:09:30.030 --> 00:09:33.660
from Tufts University,
coined this term.

00:09:33.660 --> 00:09:36.810
He said antibiotics
are "societal drugs."

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:39.510
So what he was trying
to do was explain

00:09:39.510 --> 00:09:42.970
that antibiotics are different
from any other drugs that we use.

00:09:42.970 --> 00:09:44.790
And I'd like to start
with a counterexample.

00:09:44.790 --> 00:09:47.360
So Tylenol is not a societal drug.

00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:50.330
People take Tylenol for headaches.

00:09:50.330 --> 00:09:53.080
If you misuse Tylenol,
if you overuse it,

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:57.380 position:56%
if you use it while you're drinking,
you can get liver damage and die.

00:09:57.380 --> 00:10:00.950
People commit suicide, a horrible
suicide using lots of Tylenol.

00:10:00.950 --> 00:10:02.860
But it does affect
anybody else's ability

00:10:02.860 --> 00:10:05.210
to take Tylenol for a headache.

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:09.350
However, if you misuse antibiotics,
you can drive the bacteria

00:10:09.350 --> 00:10:12.750
in your system, in your gut, on
your skin, to become resistant

00:10:12.750 --> 00:10:15.540
to antibiotics and you can share
those bacteria with other people,

00:10:15.540 --> 00:10:18.370
preventing them from
using those same drugs.

00:10:18.370 --> 00:10:20.730
So that's what Stuart
was trying to convey

00:10:20.730 --> 00:10:24.040 position:56%
with this idea of the societal drug.

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:27.600
Now, when you think about
that societal nature,

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:30.840
you have to recognize that
the context and the quantity

00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:33.940
of antibiotics that we're
using really matters.

00:10:33.940 --> 00:10:36.450
And I think the thing
that people think of most

00:10:36.450 --> 00:10:40.140
of the time is this context, right,
