00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:27.140
around these factory farms --

00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:30.100
or, sorry, around these
industrial farms.

00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:35.090
We detect lots and lots of
drug-resistant bacteria.

00:13:35.090 --> 00:13:37.870
Now, one of the things that
we use the antibiotics for,

00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:39.170
and one of the major things

00:13:39.170 --> 00:13:41.370
that we have historically
used antibiotics for,

00:13:41.370 --> 00:13:43.380
was to make animals grow faster.

00:13:43.380 --> 00:13:45.440
So we give them low
doses of antibiotics.

00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:47.200
This was discovered in the 1940s.

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:50.460
Like right after Alexander
Fleming discovered antibiotics,

00:13:50.460 --> 00:13:52.500
someone discovered that
giving animals low doses

00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:54.280
of antibiotics helps
them grow faster.

00:13:54.280 --> 00:13:55.580
We don't really understand.

00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:58.600
Probably changing the microbiome;
that is the gut community

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:01.830
of bacteria, passing more
energy onto the animal.

00:14:01.830 --> 00:14:06.370
But we don't exactly know how
well it works, and how it works.

00:14:06.370 --> 00:14:11.750
But the other justified
use is preventing diseases.

00:14:11.750 --> 00:14:14.320
But some of the diseases we're
preventing are what we call

00:14:14.320 --> 00:14:17.400
"production diseases," that
is diseases that are occurring

00:14:17.400 --> 00:14:19.360
because of the way we're
raising these animals.

00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:21.360
So I'll give you a
couple of examples.

00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:25.120 position:56%
So one of the things that we have a
lot of is shipping fever and cattle.

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:29.400
So it turns out that when you raise
animals, you let the animals graze,

00:14:29.400 --> 00:14:32.740
you have to then get them to
those feed lots, and you put them

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:34.480
in these trucks to get
them to those feedlots,

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:37.000
and sometimes you're
shipping them for days.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:40.410
And you stack them
up two layers high.

00:14:40.410 --> 00:14:41.900
These are cattle actually in this.

00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:44.280
This is what it looks
like when you empty it.

00:14:44.280 --> 00:14:46.960
And so it doesn't take
a microbiologist

00:14:46.960 --> 00:14:50.830
