00:15:37.170 --> 00:15:41.130
Okay; so here's a problem,
I think in Fisher-Price.

00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:45.100
Maybe that's not a problem, but the
public health problem that I want

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:47.420
to describe is that you --

00:15:47.420 --> 00:15:51.340
each animals has trillions of
bacteria living in and on it.

00:15:51.340 --> 00:15:55.420 position:56%
So that's not trillions, but I don't
have enough pixels to draw this.

00:15:55.420 --> 00:15:58.560 position:56%
But anyway, the animal has trillions
of bacteria living in and on it.

00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:00.600
And when you feed them
antibiotics, you're going to force

00:16:00.600 --> 00:16:04.110
that evolutionary process to
take place in those animals.

00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:06.430
Ad so the bacterial
become resistant.

00:16:06.430 --> 00:16:09.320
And then when you chop up those
