detect these things.

00:20:39.720 --> 00:20:42.760
They're silent person-to-person
transmission.

00:20:42.760 --> 00:20:45.970
You come home from your
trip to India, or China,

00:20:45.970 --> 00:20:50.130
or the United States, and you
bring home drug-resistant bacteria

00:20:50.130 --> 00:20:53.300 position:56%
and share them with your family
members, and no one knows it, right,

00:20:53.300 --> 00:20:57.860
until their immune
system is knocked down.

00:20:57.860 --> 00:20:59.750
We don't know how long
they can colonize.

00:20:59.750 --> 00:21:03.490
We know that they can
be from days to years.

00:21:03.490 --> 00:21:05.280
And then it's really difficult

00:21:05.280 --> 00:21:07.200
because you can have
animals carry them,

00:21:07.200 --> 00:21:09.350
you can have humans carry
them, you can have environment,

00:21:09.350 --> 00:21:11.320
water, carrying these bacteria.

00:21:11.320 --> 00:21:13.100
So these are really hard to study.

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:15.920
And I like a good challenge,
